# Second-Hand Market

A console-based second-hand marketplace application built in C# as part of the Backend Programming course (1st Year, Oslo). Users can register accounts, list items for sale, browse and search listings, purchase items, and leave reviews for sellers.

---

## How to Build and Run

### Prerequisites
- [.NET 8 SDK](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download) or later

### Steps

```bash
# Clone or unzip the project, then navigate to the folder
cd SecondHandMarket

# Run the application
dotnet run
```

No external dependencies or NuGet packages are required.

---

## How to Use

When you start the application you will see the guest menu:

```
=== Second-Hand Market ===
1. Register
2. Log In
3. Exit
```

- **Register** to create a new account
- **Log In** with an existing account
- Once logged in, use the main menu to create listings, browse, search, purchase items, and view your profile

