## Project Structure

```
SecondHandMarket/
├── Enums.cs          # Category, Condition, ListingStatus enums
├── User.cs           # User model with profile data and average rating
├── Listing.cs        # Listing model with auto-incrementing ID
├── Transaction.cs    # Records a completed purchase between buyer and seller
├── Review.cs         # Terningkast review left after a purchase
├── Marketplace.cs    # Core logic: registration, search, purchase, reviews
├── ConsoleUI.cs      # All console input/output and menu navigation
└── Program.cs        # Entry point — wires everything together
```

Design Decisions
Separation of concerns: Model classes hold data only. Marketplace handles logic. ConsoleUI handles all input/output. No Console.WriteLine in model classes.
Enums: Used for Category, Condition, and ListingStatus to prevent invalid values and improve readability.
LINQ: Used in Marketplace for all filtering, searching, and average calculations instead of manual loops.
Exception handling: Marketplace throws InvalidOperationException for illegal operations (e.g. buying your own listing). ConsoleUI catches these and shows friendly messages.
No inheritance: No natural "is-a" relationship existed between domain entities, so inheritance was intentionally omitted.

